Package com.cyc.baseclient.parser

Provides classes for parsing the CycL language; this code is not supported for external developers.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CycLParserConstants
    Token literal values and constants.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CycLParserTokenManager
    Token Manager.
    CycLParserUtil
    CycLParserUtil is designed to be the main entry point into parsing CycL expressions.
    SimpleCharStream
    An implementation of interface CharStream, where the stream is assumed to contain only ASCII characters (without unicode processing).
    Token
    Describes the input token stream.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    InvalidConstantGuidException
    Thrown whenever the CycL parser tries to parse a constant by its GuidImpl, and the Cyc server does not already have a constant by that GuidImpl defined.
    InvalidConstantNameException
    Thrown whenever the CycL parser tries to parse a constant by its name, and the Cyc server does not already have a constant by that name defined.
    ParseException
    This exception is thrown when parse errors are encountered.
    UnsupportedVocabularyException
    Provides
  • Error Summary 
    Error Description
    TokenMgrError
    Token Manager Error.
